title: Mosquito Alert: Insect Populations (Mosquitos)
description: Data from the Mosquito Alert Project pulled from GBIF
dataStream.name: 0c9472e1-9c8a-4a86-bb66-6d563237ea52-species occurrence
dataStream.description: All species occurrence observations from a particular user taken with a sensor or manually
dataStream.unitOfTruth: {"name":"truth observation" | "description": "whether a tiger mosquito is present"}
omProcess.license.licenseAttributionSour: This data set has been created through the efforts of the Mosquito Alert team and the thousands of citizen scientists who have volunteered their energy and contributed reports on the Mosquito Alert platform. We ask that you give attribution to the Mosquito Alert Community if you use this data in any publications.
omProcess.license.licenseAttributionAggr: Mosquito Alert, Escobar A, Oltra A (2018). Mosquito Alert: Tiger Mosquito Dataset. Version 1.6. CREAF - Centre de Recerca Ecològica i Aplicacions Forestals. Occurrence dataset https://doi.org/10.15470/t5a1os accessed via GBIF.org on 2020-08-11.
omProcess.processReference: For information on sampling methods, go to http://www.mosquitoalert.com
omProcess.resultQuality.validationMethod: The dataset includes reports from anonymous Mosquito Alert citizen scientists  tagged by them as 'adult mosquito', that contain at least one picture and that it has been evaluated by entomological experts. According to these experts, the picture/s of this observation could be tiger mosquito (Aedes albopictus): their taxonomic features can be clearly seen in the picture/s, especially the white stripe on head and thorax (confirmed; see dynamicProperties field); or only some characteristic features can be observed, but it could be this species nonetheless (probable; see dynamicProperties field). For more information, go to www.mosquitoalert.com
omProcess_resultQuality_assessment: Identification data removed to enable anonymity based on User Preference
observedProperty.name: species occurrence
observedProperty.description: whether a species is observed at a location
sensor.name: 0c9472e1-9c8a-4a86-bb66-6d563237ea52
location.name: varies
location.description: Latitude and longitude of report location in decimal degrees. Mosquito Alert anonymous citizen scientists select, via the Mosquito Alert app, the location on a map, or use GPS and other Smartphone services to record their current location at the time of the observation. Accuracy or precision of the coordinates cannot be specified for each particular case, because it depends on many factors (each participant's device, specific day of recording, network coverage, GPS availability, etc.).
thing.name: 0c9472e1-9c8a-4a86-bb66-6d563237ea52
featureOfInterest.name: location.name
informationWithheld: This dataset is a simplified version of the original one. We have removed non-biological information, information that could compromise citizen scientists’ privacy and some redundant information.

dataStream.name: e52a8d45-bc46-43a7-94bc-26841fa85d29-species occurrence
dataStream.description: All species occurrence observations from a particular user taken with a sensor or manually
dataStream.unitOfTruth: {"name":"truth observation" | "description": "whether a tiger mosquito is present"}
omProcess.license.licenseAttributionSour: This data set has been created through the efforts of the Mosquito Alert team and the thousands of citizen scientists who have volunteered their energy and contributed reports on the Mosquito Alert platform. We ask that you give attribution to the Mosquito Alert Community if you use this data in any publications.
omProcess.license.licenseAttributionAggr: Mosquito Alert, Escobar A, Oltra A (2018). Mosquito Alert: Tiger Mosquito Dataset. Version 1.6. CREAF - Centre de Recerca Ecològica i Aplicacions Forestals. Occurrence dataset https://doi.org/10.15470/t5a1os accessed via GBIF.org on 2020-08-11.
omProcess.processReference: For information on sampling methods, go to http://www.mosquitoalert.com
omProcess.resultQuality.validationMethod: The dataset includes reports from anonymous Mosquito Alert citizen scientists  tagged by them as 'adult mosquito', that contain at least one picture and that it has been evaluated by entomological experts. According to these experts, the picture/s of this observation could be tiger mosquito (Aedes albopictus): their taxonomic features can be clearly seen in the picture/s, especially the white stripe on head and thorax (confirmed; see dynamicProperties field); or only some characteristic features can be observed, but it could be this species nonetheless (probable; see dynamicProperties field). For more information, go to www.mosquitoalert.com
omProcess_resultQuality_assessment: Identification data removed to enable anonymity based on User Preference
observedProperty.name: species occurrence
observedProperty.description: whether a species is observed at a location
sensor.name: e52a8d45-bc46-43a7-94bc-26841fa85d29
location.name: varies
location.description: Latitude and longitude of report location in decimal degrees. Mosquito Alert anonymous citizen scientists select, via the Mosquito Alert app, the location on a map, or use GPS and other Smartphone services to record their current location at the time of the observation. Accuracy or precision of the coordinates cannot be specified for each particular case, because it depends on many factors (each participant's device, specific day of recording, network coverage, GPS availability, etc.).
thing.name: e52a8d45-bc46-43a7-94bc-26841fa85d29
featureOfInterest.name: location.name
informationWithheld: This dataset is a simplified version of the original one. We have removed non-biological information, information that could compromise citizen scientists’ privacy and some redundant information.

omProcess.processReference: For information on sampling methods, go to http://www.mosquitoalert.com
omProcess.resultQuality.validationMethod: The dataset includes reports from anonymous Mosquito Alert citizen scientists  tagged by them as 'adult mosquito', that contain at least one picture and that it has been evaluated by entomological experts. According to these experts, the picture/s of this observation could be tiger mosquito (Aedes albopictus): their taxonomic features can be clearly seen in the picture/s, especially the white stripe on head and thorax (confirmed; see dynamicProperties field); or only some characteristic features can be observed, but it could be this species nonetheless (probable; see dynamicProperties field). For more information, go to www.mosquitoalert.com
omProcess_resultQuality_assessment: Identification data removed to enable anonymity based on User Preference
observedProperty.name: species occurrence

sensor.name: fa5b2500-9ae0-4c2f-956f-d7bef28b0c4a
location.name: varies
location.description: Latitude and longitude of report location in decimal degrees. Mosquito Alert anonymous citizen scientists select, via the Mosquito Alert app, the location on a map, or use GPS and other Smartphone services to record their current location at the time of the observation. Accuracy or precision of the coordinates cannot be specified for each particular case, because it depends on many factors (each participant's device, specific day of recording, network coverage, GPS availability, etc.).
thing.name: fa5b2500-9ae0-4c2f-956f-d7bef28b0c4a
